SELECT pd.patient_name, COUNT(DISTINCT mu.medication_name) AS unique_medications FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY pd.patient_name HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT mu.medication_name) >= 3;

SELECT patient_name, AVG(adherence_rate) AS avg_adherence, MAX(adherence_rate) AS max_adherence FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY patient_name HAVING AVG(adherence_rate) < 0.9;

SELECT pd.patient_name, COUNT(mu.medication_name) AS total_medications FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY pd.patient_name HAVING COUNT(mu.medication_name) <= 5;
SELECT pd.patient_name, SUM(mu.dosage) AS total_dosage FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY pd.patient_name HAVING SUM(mu.dosage) > 100;

SELECT pd.patient_name, AVG(mu.dosage) AS avg_dosage, MAX(mu.dosage) AS max_dosage FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY pd.patient_name HAVING AVG(mu.dosage) > 50 AND MAX(mu.dosage) < 200;

SELECT pd.patient_name, COUNT(*) AS total_records, AVG(mu.dosage) AS avg_dosage FROM MedicationUsage mu JOIN PatientDemographics pd ON mu.patient_id = pd.patient_id GROUP BY pd.patient_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 2 AND AVG(mu.dosage) < 100;
